Why camera inverted why!?

To be fair, the sound effects are brilliant. The transitions between vision modes are good too, and the lock on feature is cool, however that is where the positives end.  The camera view is always inverted regardless of out-app setting adjustments. Not to mention the lock on feature doesn't turn off unless you close the app and reload it.  The three vision modes avaliable are blue/orange/gray, the colored filters are so prominant that you can barely make out basic shapes (like doorways). I also expected a green alien filter, a bit bummed that there wasn't one. Adding a record feature would be brilliant as well.   To conclude this app has potential to be really good, if the creator took a little time to improve it. It's only £1.50, not much however it's not worth that amount of money. If the issues listed were to be fixed I'd be willing to spend at least  £5.
